{"componentChunkName":"component---src-layouts-blog-post-layout-js","path":"/blog/how-to-add-name-field-to-newsletter-free-themes","result":{"pageContext":{"id":3220,"date":"2023-08-31T07:55:06","date_gmt":"2023-08-31T07:55:06","guid":{"rendered":"https://www.ezfy.club/?p=3220"},"modified":"2024-03-03T22:46:30","modified_gmt":"2024-03-03T22:46:30","slug":"how-to-add-name-field-to-newsletter-free-themes","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://www.ezfy.club/how-to-add-name-field-to-newsletter-free-themes/","title":{"rendered":"How to add a &#8220;name&#8221; field to the newsletter section [all free themes]"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"How to add a “first name” field to the email signup section\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/YhFvHX_Df24?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Addressing people by their name is always a sign of respect and personal connection. This is no different when it comes to email marketing. An email&#8217;s subject line like &#8220;Hey John, check this new product out!&#8221; is much more powerful than &#8220;Hey, check this new product out!&#8221;.<br><br>Even though this is an important aspect of email marketing, Shopify&#8217;s official free themes (like Dawn) do not come with any built-in options to add a &#8220;first name&#8221; field, which can take a considerate toll on merchants&#8217; email marketing strategies. There&#8217;s much less room to explore creative personalization messages.<br><br>Therefore, in today&#8217;s blog post, we&#8217;ll teach you how to quickly add a &#8220;name&#8221; field to your theme&#8217;s newsletter, both the newsletter section and the footer.<br><br>In case you&#8217;re curious, <a href=\"https://pandashopdeals.myshopify.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here is a live demo of how the end result will look like.</a><br><br>So, without further ado, let&#8217;s dive in.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"NoticeBox NoticeBox--info\"><p>This tutorial is compatible only with Shopify&#8217;s official free themes: <b>Dawn, Refresh, Colorblock, Taste, Ride, Studio, Crave, Origin, Spotlight, Publisher, Sense &amp; Craft.</b></p></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Before diving into the tutorial make sure you download the theme, so in case you face any issues you can easily revert back.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1514\" height=\"481\" class=\"wp-image-503\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123.png 1514w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-600x191.png 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-1200x381.png 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-768x244.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1514px) 100vw, 1514px\" /></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-adding-the-name-field-to-the-newsletter-section\">Adding the name field to the newsletter section</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>From your Shopify admin, go to&nbsp;<strong>Online Store</strong>&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Themes&nbsp;</strong>&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Actions&nbsp;</strong>&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Edit Code</strong>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Find&nbsp;the <strong>newsletter.liquid</strong> file.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Press <strong>CTRL + F</strong> (or <strong>command + F</strong> on Mac) and search for exactly this (quotes included):<br><br><strong>class=&#8221;field&#8221;</strong><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Paste the following code <strong>above</strong> the line found:<br><br>[gist]d9bd78f4e853aab3e3128a46d992186b[gist]<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1001\" height=\"784\" class=\"wp-image-3691\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/s0.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/s0.jpg 1001w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/s0-850x666.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/s0-768x602.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1001px) 100vw, 1001px\" /><br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1052\" height=\"853\" class=\"wp-image-3693\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/s1.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/s1.jpg 1052w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/s1-850x689.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/s1-768x623.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1052px) 100vw, 1052px\" /><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Perfect! If you&#8217;d like to add it to the footer&#8217;s newsletter as well, repeat the exact same steps but inside the file <strong>footer.liquid</strong></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-ok-but-how-do-i-view-the-customers-first-name-and-email-now\">Ok, but how do I view the customers&#8217; first name and email now?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>From your <strong>Shopify Admin</strong>, click on the &#8220;Customers&#8221; tab on the left side. In there you&#8217;ll be able to view all of your registered customers.<br><br>Once you click on one of them, then you&#8217;ll be able to view their email and other pertinent information.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1099\" height=\"454\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/image-3.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1210\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/image-3.png 1099w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/image-3-850x351.png 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/image-3-768x317.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1099px) 100vw, 1099px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"487\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/image-1-1200x487.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1206\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/image-1-1200x487.png 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/image-1-850x345.png 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/image-1-768x312.png 768w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/image-1.png 1207w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That is it, now you can capture your audience&#8217;s name and emails!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"you-may-also-like\">You may also like</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some other tutorials you may be interested in. They work with &#8220;Dawn&#8221; plus all Shopify&#8217;s free themes (Craft, Refresh, Colorblock, Taste, Ride, Studio, Crave, Origin, Spotlight, Publisher &amp; Sense):<br><a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/blog/dawn-theme-product-page-slideshow-with-arrows-tutorial\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">&#8211; Arrows &amp; vertical thumbnails for Dawn&#8217;s product pages<span><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media3.giphy.com/media/w4LaQF8cp1akInO4Cp/giphy.gif\"></span></a><br><a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/blog/dawn-theme-how-to-fix-zoom-images-size-mobile-desktop?source=blog-dawn\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">&#8211; Dawn lightbox: responsive images, slider and arrows <span><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media4.giphy.com/media/aBmvXTlfvHiPMXtx4a/giphy.gif\"></span></a><br><a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/blog/how-to-disable-right-click-image-and-text-copying-without-apps?source=blog-dawn\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">&#8211; Improve your website&#8217;s safety: block right click, image copying and more</a></p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Add a &#8